  "prompt": "What is the best TOR directory with active links and intelligent queries?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Tor (The Onion Router) is a network designed for privacy and anonymity, and it hosts various directories and services accessible through the Tor Browser. However, the landscape of active Tor directories and services can change frequently due to the nature of the network.\n\nHere are some well-known directories and search engines that have been historically active and useful for finding Tor hidden services (\".onion\" sites):\n\n1. **Ahmia** (https://ahmia.fi)\n   - Ahmia is a search engine for the Tor network that focuses on indexing legitimate and legal content. It provides a curated list of active onion sites and is known for its intelligent queries and filtering mechanisms to avoid illegal content.\n\n2. **Torch** (http://xmh57jrzrnw6insl.onion)\n   - Torch is one of the oldest and most popular search engines on the Tor network. It indexes a wide range of onion sites and is often used by those looking to explore the deep web.\n\n3. **Haystak** (http://haystak5njsmn2hqkewecpaxetahtwhsbsa64jom2k22z5afxhnpxfid.onion)\n   - Haystak is another search engine designed specifically for the Tor network. It claims to have a large index of onion sites and offers features like filtering by content type.\n\n4. **DuckDuckGo** (https://3g2upl4pq6kufc4m.onion)\n   - DuckDuckGo is a privacy-focused search engine that offers an onion service. While it primarily searches the clearnet, it also provides results for some hidden services and is known for its intelligent query handling.\n\n5. **OnionLand Search** (http://3bbad7fauom4d6sgppalyqddsqbf5u5p56b5k5uk2zxsy3d6ey2jobad.onion)\n   - OnionLand is a search engine that indexes Tor hidden services. It provides a simple interface and claims to have indexed a significant number of onion sites.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Legality and Safety**: Always be cautious when exploring the Tor network. Many sites indexed by these directories may be illegal or unsafe. Stick to legal content and use good security practices.\n- **Verification**: Ensure that you are accessing the correct onion URLs to avoid phishing or malicious sites. Always verify URLs from trusted sources.\n- **Updates**: The Tor network is dynamic, so some directories may become inactive or change their URLs over time. Always check for the latest information from reliable sources.\n\nFor the most up-to-date information, consider visiting forums and communities focused on Tor usage, such as Reddit\u2019s r/onions or other privacy-focused communities.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
